1
00:00:00,133 --> 00:00:01,568
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,568 --> 00:00:03,036
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:04,639 --> 00:00:06,439
What do we do?
Eun Nim isn't answering her phone.

4
00:00:06,773 --> 00:00:08,475
Mom and Dad are probably asleep by now.

5
00:00:10,167 --> 00:00:12,067
She's probably so focused
on her serialization right now...

6
00:00:12,067 --> 00:00:14,467
that she hasn't seen it.
I'll send her a text.

7
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,800
She'll probably check it before bed.

8
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,151
At this rate,
we might end up sleeping in the yard.

9
00:00:18,151 --> 00:00:20,420
What? It'd be freezing.

10
00:00:21,767 --> 00:00:23,800
All right, let's see your phone now,
Team Manager.

11
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:26,260
- Come on, hurry up.
- What? I'd rather not show you.

12
00:00:26,667 --> 00:00:27,667
Let me see.

13
00:00:31,465 --> 00:00:32,866
(Childish Bunny)

14
00:00:32,866 --> 00:00:35,402
Wait, "Childish Bunny?"

15
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,971
You saved me as that because I'm childish?

16
00:00:37,971 --> 00:00:39,467
No, that's not it.

17
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:42,076
Remember what you said
when you got out of the holding cell?

18
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:45,445
- I'm...
- I'm a very weak...

19
00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,180
and fragile bunny.

20
00:00:47,267 --> 00:00:50,217
A very weak and fragile bunny.

21
00:00:51,567 --> 00:00:54,667
So I meant
a bunny fresh out of the holding cell.

22
00:00:54,667 --> 00:00:55,789
Something like that.

23
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:57,024
Change it right now.

24
00:00:57,167 --> 00:01:00,194
How can you use that awful holding cell
in my contact name?

25
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,667
Then what should I change it to?

26
00:01:01,667 --> 00:01:04,398
Flying Kick Cho Eun Ae?
Or Drunk Cho Eun Ae?

27
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:06,233
Seriously.

28
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,738
You even have a video?

29
00:01:19,367 --> 00:01:20,800
Delete this right now.

30
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:22,416
Delete this one first!

31
00:01:22,978 --> 00:01:24,918
What's with you?
Digging through someone else's phone...

32
00:01:24,918 --> 00:01:26,553
is a violation
of information network laws.

33
00:01:26,867 --> 00:01:28,467
There you go again with the laws.

34
00:01:28,467 --> 00:01:30,324
- Seriously, delete this.
- What is wrong with you?

35
00:01:30,324 --> 00:01:31,658
Wait, hold on...

36
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:43,604
I said delete it.

37
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:46,707
Well...

38
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:52,413
Why would I delete it? It's my lullaby.

39
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:54,515
A lullaby? At your age?

40
00:01:55,467 --> 00:01:57,484
Has Eun Nim still not seen the text?

41
00:01:58,452 --> 00:02:01,488
Why bother her when she's working hard?

42
00:02:01,488 --> 00:02:02,823
She'll open the door eventually.

43
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:04,467
I guess so.

44
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:08,662
Are you cold? Want my jacket?

45
00:02:08,662 --> 00:02:10,531
No. You're cold too.

46
00:02:15,700 --> 00:02:16,970
Want to share this blanket?

47
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:18,905
Sounds good.

48
00:02:26,079 --> 00:02:28,081
The night air feels nice and cool.

49
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:32,052
Probably because the air is so clean
after the rain.

50
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:35,867
Are you sleepy?

51
00:02:36,767 --> 00:02:40,527
No. I think it's just my body telling me
it's time to sleep out of habit.

52
00:02:40,794 --> 00:02:42,667
How about borrowing my shoulder?

53
00:02:43,467 --> 00:02:45,666
Excuse me? No thanks.

54
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,212
Cho Eun Ae? Team Manager Ko?

55
00:03:05,767 --> 00:03:06,887
Dad.

56
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:13,627
Honey, on your way back from exercising,
could you grab some milk...

57
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:17,331
What are you all doing out here
so early in the morning?

58
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,000
Well...

59
00:03:26,767 --> 00:03:27,808
Eun Hyeong.

60
00:03:29,076 --> 00:03:30,844
Hello, Mom, Dad.

61
00:03:31,078 --> 00:03:32,412
Grandma.

62
00:03:33,267 --> 00:03:34,782
My little puppy's here.

63
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:38,185
What brings you here at this hour?

64
00:03:38,785 --> 00:03:39,920
And what's with that bag?

65
00:03:41,867 --> 00:03:44,167
I was hoping you could watch Bit Na
for a few days.

66
00:03:44,167 --> 00:03:45,167
Are you going somewhere?

67
00:03:46,767 --> 00:03:48,962
I thought Ji Seon switched
to an office position.

68
00:03:50,367 --> 00:03:52,700
Let's go inside first
instead of standing out here.

69
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,369
- Right. Everyone, come on in.
- Get inside.

70
00:03:56,536 --> 00:03:58,105
Bit Na, you haven't had breakfast yet,
have you?

71
00:03:58,105 --> 00:03:59,267
- No, Grandma.
- Get inside.

72
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,745
What happened to you two?

73
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:06,667
Well...

74
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:10,016
Dad, you're late.
You should get ready for work.

75
00:04:11,867 --> 00:04:13,020
What are you doing? Come inside.

76
00:04:19,767 --> 00:04:21,028
This is my Team Manager.

77
00:04:21,628 --> 00:04:23,767
He moved into your old room.

78
00:04:23,767 --> 00:04:24,767
This is my big brother.

79
00:04:24,767 --> 00:04:26,567
I see. Hello, I'm Ko Gyeol.

80
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:27,967
Hello, I'm Cho Eun Hyeong.

81
00:04:28,367 --> 00:04:29,967
- I'll head in first.
- Okay.

82
00:04:31,967 --> 00:04:33,200
What happened?

83
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:35,167
Did we both fall asleep...

84
00:04:35,167 --> 00:04:36,667
while waiting for Eun Nim
to open the door?

85
00:04:37,167 --> 00:04:38,278
I think so.

86
00:04:38,567 --> 00:04:41,148
But your father won't get the wrong idea,
right?

87
00:04:41,367 --> 00:04:44,585
What wrong idea? Cho Eun Nim, this girl...

88
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,123
What's wrong? Did you catch a cold?

89
00:05:01,601 --> 00:05:03,236
I can't believe this.

90
00:05:08,275 --> 00:05:09,743
Bit Na's mom is going on a business trip?

91
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:13,147
But she works in the office.

92
00:05:13,367 --> 00:05:15,549
Even office staff
go on business trips sometimes.

93
00:05:16,367 --> 00:05:18,151
My classes end late at night,

94
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:19,753
so please watch Bit Na for a few days.

95
00:05:20,053 --> 00:05:21,521
That's no trouble at all.

96
00:05:23,867 --> 00:05:25,425
There isn't some other problem, is there?

97
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,861
No. What other problem could there be?

98
00:05:29,229 --> 00:05:31,698
Mom's apples...

99
00:05:32,367 --> 00:05:34,367
Apples? Bit Na, do you want an apple?

100
00:05:35,200 --> 00:05:36,570
Okay.

101
00:05:36,903 --> 00:05:39,606
I'll peel one for you after breakfast.

102
00:05:42,367 --> 00:05:44,300
I'll set the table.
You should go wash up too.

103
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:45,378
Okay.

104
00:05:47,167 --> 00:05:48,167
I almost forgot.

105
00:05:48,867 --> 00:05:50,717
Can we go see that place this morning?

106
00:05:52,419 --> 00:05:55,267
Not today. I'll schedule another time.

107
00:05:55,567 --> 00:05:56,567
All right then.

108
00:05:58,667 --> 00:06:00,867
Mom went to look for apples.

109
00:06:01,167 --> 00:06:03,163
Why did you lie, Dad?

110
00:06:04,067 --> 00:06:07,467
Mom will find lots and lots of apples,

111
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:10,067
and she's going to surprise
Grandma and Grandpa.

112
00:06:10,067 --> 00:06:11,067
So until then, it's a secret.

113
00:06:11,367 --> 00:06:13,067
Okay, Dad.

114
00:06:17,867 --> 00:06:19,279
Is Mother very ill?

115
00:06:20,267 --> 00:06:22,816
I've never seen her unable
to get out of bed in the morning.

116
00:06:25,318 --> 00:06:27,854
How exactly
has Mr. Seo been handling things?

117
00:06:28,967 --> 00:06:30,824
I'll have a serious talk with him today.

118
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:32,859
Stay out of it, CEO Ko.

119
00:06:33,567 --> 00:06:35,067
Why interfere in something you don't know?

120
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:39,700
Father,
you should just tell him everything.

121
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:42,267
We're the only ones
not being told anything.

122
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:43,937
How are we supposed to know?

123
00:06:47,274 --> 00:06:48,800
Breakfast is ready.

124
00:06:49,100 --> 00:06:52,079
Thank you. Father, please come eat.

125
00:06:52,700 --> 00:06:54,067
I'm not hungry.

126
00:06:55,215 --> 00:06:58,200
Father, you need to eat
before taking your medicine.

127
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,921
I'll eat later with your mother.

128
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,656
You eat and get to work.

129
00:07:06,006 --> 00:07:07,006
What...

130
00:07:07,386 --> 00:07:09,586
Why are you all standing here?
Aren't you eating?

131
00:07:09,967 --> 00:07:11,965
What are you talking about?
Of course we are.

132
00:07:12,300 --> 00:07:14,667
Son, go eat. You too, honey.

133
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:15,667
Yes, Mom.

134
00:07:16,703 --> 00:07:20,674
Crystal, could you maybe
work on your expression a little?

135
00:07:20,967 --> 00:07:22,509
Why? What's wrong with my expression?

136
00:07:22,709 --> 00:07:25,612
You sound worried,
but your eyes are smiling.

137
00:07:26,867 --> 00:07:27,867
Was it that obvious?

138
00:07:29,082 --> 00:07:30,617
I'll be more careful.

139
00:07:34,988 --> 00:07:38,358
How can she be so transparent?

140
00:07:38,926 --> 00:07:39,926
She never changes.

141
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:43,997
Why did you get up
instead of sleeping more?

142
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:45,932
I slept enough.

143
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:49,202
You need to take your morning medicine.

144
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,371
You should eat first.

145
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:53,774
Stop worrying about me and sit down.

146
00:07:58,386 --> 00:08:00,286
Just one day,
and your face already looks...

147
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:03,917
This is why I wanted to look
without you knowing.

148
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:07,421
It's not like this is the first time
we've been through this.

149
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:11,324
I was just too impatient this time.

150
00:08:12,580 --> 00:08:15,447
This isn't your fault, so don't worry.

151
00:08:16,452 --> 00:08:17,452
Yeong Hwa.

152
00:08:18,367 --> 00:08:20,634
We'll find her. We definitely will.

153
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,467
Before I leave this world,

154
00:08:24,200 --> 00:08:26,567
I'll keep that promise no matter what.

155
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:29,800
Can you stay too,

156
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:33,367
and meet Yeon Sun?

157
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:36,767
Isn't that possible?

158
00:08:37,539 --> 00:08:38,539
I'm sorry.

159
00:08:40,095 --> 00:08:41,267
I'm so sorry to you.

160
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:44,667
No words can express it.

161
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:47,728
No matter what happened back then,

162
00:08:48,867 --> 00:08:50,497
I should've taken Yeon Sun with us.

163
00:08:51,167 --> 00:08:54,000
If only I'd gone looking for her sooner.

164
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:01,975
Excuse me, what happened?

165
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:03,844
Where did the original owners go?

166
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:07,367
Why? Did they scam you too?

167
00:09:07,367 --> 00:09:08,827
- Sorry?
- That couple...

168
00:09:08,827 --> 00:09:11,151
took people's money
and ran away in the middle of the night.

169
00:09:11,999 --> 00:09:13,553
They ran away in the middle of the night?

170
00:09:14,485 --> 00:09:15,552
Then what about my daughter?

171
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,367
My Yeon Sun. Where is she?

172
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:19,626
How would I know?

173
00:09:19,959 --> 00:09:22,695
I only bought this restaurant
at an auction recently.

174
00:09:29,500 --> 00:09:31,237
Yeong Hwa, are you okay?

175
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,639
What about Yeon Sun?

176
00:09:33,567 --> 00:09:35,642
Don't worry, Yeong Hwa.

177
00:09:36,067 --> 00:09:38,867
No matter what it takes,

178
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:40,347
I'll find Yeon Sun. I promise.

179
00:09:40,347 --> 00:09:41,915
What about Yeon Sun?

180
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:45,767
My Yeon Sun...

181
00:09:46,812 --> 00:09:48,667
- Yeon Sun!
- Yeong Hwa.

182
00:09:49,267 --> 00:09:50,267
Yeong Hwa.

183
00:09:51,167 --> 00:09:52,592
I'm sorry.

184
00:09:53,267 --> 00:09:56,897
I shouldn't be like this in front of you,
but the tears just won't stop.

185
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:10,076
It's rice gruel.

186
00:10:10,267 --> 00:10:12,612
You need to eat this
and get your strength back.

187
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,815
Thank you.

188
00:10:16,267 --> 00:10:19,600
Mother, please think of me
as your daughter from now on,

189
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,854
and let it go.

190
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:23,089
I'll be a good daughter to you.

191
00:10:25,867 --> 00:10:29,062
You know what they say,
"Water is thicker than blood."

192
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:30,430
Enough!

193
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:32,961
I'm sorry.

194
00:10:32,961 --> 00:10:34,634
Please have some gruel, Mother.

195
00:10:37,073 --> 00:10:39,506
How can someone be so thoughtless?

196
00:10:40,867 --> 00:10:42,375
You should eat the gruel.

197
00:10:43,191 --> 00:10:45,000
You can't skip your medicine.

198
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,646
Right. Let's eat.

199
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:55,915
Maybe I should send this back
through Seong Jun.

200
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:00,594
Apparently, it was Madam's daughter.

201
00:11:01,728 --> 00:11:04,397
But CEO Ko is supposed
to be the Chairman's only child.

202
00:11:05,067 --> 00:11:07,667
I have no idea what happened.

203
00:11:09,267 --> 00:11:11,438
People's lives are all the same.

204
00:11:12,413 --> 00:11:15,008
Once you look closely,
every family has its own story.

205
00:11:17,177 --> 00:11:18,745
(Ham Cho Rong)

206
00:11:18,745 --> 00:11:21,114
(Grandma's Bindaetteok)

207
00:11:28,967 --> 00:11:31,191
One, two, three, four.

208
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:33,167
One, two, three, four.

209
00:11:33,167 --> 00:11:36,467
One, two, three, four. One, two, three.

210
00:11:36,467 --> 00:11:39,067
Grandma,
you've really caught the dance bug.

211
00:11:39,067 --> 00:11:40,734
What? The dance bug?

212
00:11:41,086 --> 00:11:42,646
How did you hold it in all this time?

213
00:11:45,367 --> 00:11:46,467
Yeon Ja,

214
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:49,079
can we go to the dance hall
a little early today?

215
00:11:49,079 --> 00:11:52,046
I need to get there early and practice.

216
00:11:52,700 --> 00:11:55,067
I'm sorry. I don't think I can go today.

217
00:11:55,067 --> 00:11:56,983
What are you talking about? Why not?

218
00:11:56,983 --> 00:11:58,952
I have to pick Bit Na up.

219
00:11:59,467 --> 00:12:01,367
Eun Hyeong has classes this afternoon,

220
00:12:01,367 --> 00:12:02,967
and Bit Na's mom is away
on a business trip.

221
00:12:02,967 --> 00:12:06,759
I practiced all night
so I could show off my skills...

222
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:08,966
in class today.

223
00:12:09,526 --> 00:12:12,932
You should go. Why should you miss it
just because I can't go?

224
00:12:12,932 --> 00:12:14,978
What fun would it be going alone?

225
00:12:14,978 --> 00:12:16,940
I go because we're together.

226
00:12:17,459 --> 00:12:19,185
Don't worry and go to the dance class.

227
00:12:19,185 --> 00:12:20,252
I'll watch Bit Na.

228
00:12:20,967 --> 00:12:23,543
Will you, Cho Rong? I feel bad.

229
00:12:23,985 --> 00:12:25,867
Well, that's perfect then.

230
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:27,860
We're off and running.

231
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:30,183
Straight ahead.

232
00:12:30,925 --> 00:12:31,925
Right, Sun Bun.

233
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:35,400
Try not to give that woman
such a hard time anymore.

234
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:38,158
Who? That stuck-up woman?

235
00:12:38,699 --> 00:12:41,360
Why?

236
00:12:41,847 --> 00:12:44,530
I get a real kick out of putting her
in her place.

237
00:12:44,530 --> 00:12:47,267
That woman is my husband's boss's wife.

238
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:48,935
You mean that woman...

239
00:12:49,167 --> 00:12:52,100
is the wife
of the CEO of Kangsu Construction?

240
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:54,974
Yes. If things get tense between us,

241
00:12:54,974 --> 00:12:57,666
nothing good will come of it.
I'm going to be careful too.

242
00:12:57,667 --> 00:13:00,680
Seriously, why did it have to be her?

243
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:05,029
This is bad.
That investment scam really blew up.

244
00:13:05,967 --> 00:13:07,554
What investment scam?

245
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,767
A stock-tip chatroom scam.

246
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:11,324
Looks like there are tons of victims.

247
00:13:12,067 --> 00:13:14,080
Apparently,
a lot of homemakers and young people...

248
00:13:14,080 --> 00:13:15,980
with little investing experience
got scammed.

249
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,530
That's awful.

250
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,600
They probably invested money
they worked hard to earn.

251
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,900
A chatroom? Someone was running
a scam from their room?

252
00:13:25,044 --> 00:13:26,077
Whose house?

253
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:28,842
- Not that kind of room.
- Okay.

254
00:13:29,792 --> 00:13:31,692
Never mind, Grandma. Dance away.

255
00:13:32,306 --> 00:13:35,381
Hello, Mother-in-law. Have you been well?

256
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,700
I'm sorry we don't visit more often.

257
00:13:39,486 --> 00:13:42,955
It's fine. Everyone's just busy with life.

258
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,167
I already feel bad enough...

259
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:48,367
that you secretly send spending money
every month.

260
00:13:48,832 --> 00:13:50,429
Not at all.

261
00:13:51,047 --> 00:13:53,667
I wish I could send more, but right now...

262
00:13:55,158 --> 00:13:57,537
Mother-in-law, by any chance, Ji Seon...

263
00:13:57,537 --> 00:13:58,971
Ji Seon's doing well, right?

264
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:03,176
Maybe she thinks visiting her parents
will create more worries,

265
00:14:03,767 --> 00:14:05,930
but she hardly calls these days.

266
00:14:06,667 --> 00:14:07,881
It's not like that at all.

267
00:14:08,567 --> 00:14:12,558
We'll come visit together soon.
Yes. Have a good day.

268
00:14:18,167 --> 00:14:20,597
Where on earth did you go, Cheon Ji Seon?

269
00:14:23,667 --> 00:14:25,465
Even if the scam ring gets caught,

270
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:28,334
there's no guarantee
you'll recover your investment.

271
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:31,738
Staying here won't change anything,
so please go home.

272
00:14:40,680 --> 00:14:42,749
(Honey)

273
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:49,289
What do I do?

274
00:14:50,567 --> 00:14:52,425
What am I supposed to do now?

275
00:15:01,952 --> 00:15:02,952
What happened?

276
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,405
I trusted you and invested
because of what you said.

277
00:15:06,206 --> 00:15:08,164
What on earth happened?

278
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:11,744
I'm about to lose everything
because of you!

279
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,700
What? How is that all my fault?

280
00:15:15,948 --> 00:15:19,119
I'm sorry,
but you're the one who decided to invest.

281
00:15:19,119 --> 00:15:20,286
I only gave you the information.

282
00:15:20,967 --> 00:15:22,789
How much did you lose, anyway?

283
00:15:23,367 --> 00:15:24,367
I lost 50,000.

284
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:25,467
Only 50,000?

285
00:15:25,867 --> 00:15:28,625
I thought it was going to be
hundreds of thousands.

286
00:15:28,961 --> 00:15:31,400
Anyway, good luck sorting it out.

287
00:15:31,667 --> 00:15:32,899
I'm busy right now.

288
00:15:35,367 --> 00:15:38,471
Hello? Hey!

289
00:15:40,567 --> 00:15:41,808
Only 50,000?

290
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:47,247
You have no idea what that money means!

291
00:15:49,267 --> 00:15:52,118
Do you know what that money means to us?

292
00:16:05,867 --> 00:16:08,167
(Kangsu Construction)

293
00:16:08,806 --> 00:16:10,039
Seriously.

294
00:16:10,832 --> 00:16:13,372
Are there no other sites besides these?

295
00:16:13,967 --> 00:16:18,067
Something with a great view of Hangang,
excellent transportation,

296
00:16:18,067 --> 00:16:20,213
and a perfect commercial district nearby.

297
00:16:20,700 --> 00:16:22,148
Isn't there anything like that?

298
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,600
For a location like that, you'd need...

299
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,286
to increase the budget
by at least five times.

300
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:29,700
Five times?

301
00:16:29,700 --> 00:16:33,031
That would mean
spending nearly 30 percent...

302
00:16:33,480 --> 00:16:35,440
of Kangsu Construction's annual budget
just to secure the land.

303
00:16:37,159 --> 00:16:40,132
I told you not to argue with me
so many times.

304
00:16:40,795 --> 00:16:43,436
What are you, my boss?

305
00:16:44,060 --> 00:16:45,060
My mentor?

306
00:16:45,227 --> 00:16:47,640
Why do you keep analyzing, criticizing,
and advising me?

307
00:16:49,579 --> 00:16:50,943
Dae Chi.

308
00:16:51,499 --> 00:16:52,778
Yes, Seong Jun.

309
00:16:54,313 --> 00:16:56,316
What did you say?

310
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:59,385
Did you just call me by my name, Mr. Cho?

311
00:16:59,554 --> 00:17:01,454
Yeah, I called you by your name,
Ko Dae Chi.

312
00:17:05,099 --> 00:17:07,632
Let me ask you one thing as your friend.

313
00:17:07,930 --> 00:17:11,163
Why did you hire me as your assistant?

314
00:17:12,612 --> 00:17:13,712
What are you talking about?

315
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,567
You asked me to help you.

316
00:17:16,560 --> 00:17:18,000
So despite my shortcomings,

317
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:21,708
I came here
believing I could offer advice...

318
00:17:21,986 --> 00:17:24,167
from my experience and business knowledge,

319
00:17:24,167 --> 00:17:25,545
and that you'd actually listen.

320
00:17:25,867 --> 00:17:28,767
Right. And I'm grateful for that.

321
00:17:28,767 --> 00:17:32,400
But if you're going
to completely ignore my opinions,

322
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,320
is there any reason for me to stay here?

323
00:17:34,919 --> 00:17:38,824
Mr. Cho, what's gotten into you?
You're scaring me.

324
00:17:39,466 --> 00:17:42,167
Okay, I went too far.

325
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:43,796
I apologize. I'm sorry.

326
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,866
I'll listen more carefully from now on.

327
00:17:55,213 --> 00:17:57,643
I'll look for more sites
that meet your requirements...

328
00:17:58,773 --> 00:17:59,940
and submit a revised report.

329
00:18:00,159 --> 00:18:01,247
I'm counting on you.

330
00:18:05,467 --> 00:18:06,467
This is driving me crazy.

331
00:18:06,467 --> 00:18:08,921
How does he...

332
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,524
calmly tear someone apart like that?

333
00:18:11,999 --> 00:18:14,126
He completely steamrolls me,
and I'm the CEO.

334
00:18:15,167 --> 00:18:17,130
How am I supposed to tame him?

335
00:18:17,767 --> 00:18:19,632
Why is my heart racing? He's my assistant.

336
00:18:25,567 --> 00:18:26,673
Do you have a cold?

337
00:18:27,273 --> 00:18:30,443
Excuse me? No. Maybe allergies.

338
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:36,182
Can rhinitis be contagious?

339
00:18:36,967 --> 00:18:38,651
Why are you both sneezing
at the same time?

340
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:49,729
Is there a cold going around the office
or something?

341
00:18:51,832 --> 00:18:53,532
Just say what you need to say.

342
00:18:55,600 --> 00:18:57,900
Administration requested
the budget materials...

343
00:18:57,900 --> 00:18:59,500
for the second round of evaluations.

344
00:18:59,826 --> 00:19:01,126
Yes,
I'll send them as soon as they're ready...

345
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:10,917
Everyone, be careful not to catch a cold.

346
00:19:18,406 --> 00:19:20,359
Why did it have to happen
to both of us at once?

347
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:23,496
I didn't even feel cold.

348
00:19:34,626 --> 00:19:35,841
What's this?

349
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:39,567
Cold medicine.
It's important to treat a cold early.

350
00:19:40,667 --> 00:19:42,048
Thank you, Manager Seo.

351
00:19:42,967 --> 00:19:44,767
Were you with the Team Manager yesterday?

352
00:19:45,167 --> 00:19:46,167
Sorry?

353
00:19:46,167 --> 00:19:49,344
You know there are two things
you can't hide in this world, right?

354
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:52,425
A sneeze and love.

355
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,300
Manager Seo.

356
00:19:54,867 --> 00:19:58,064
Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
do you like Team Manager Ko?

357
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,667
Do I have any reason...

358
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,072
to answer that question?

359
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:11,367
- Did you two make some kind of pact?
- What?

360
00:20:11,367 --> 00:20:13,548
I asked the Team Manager
the same question.

361
00:20:14,013 --> 00:20:15,346
Whether he likes you.

362
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,718
And he gave the exact same answer.

363
00:20:24,900 --> 00:20:25,900
Gyeol and I...

364
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,900
lived under the same roof
for over ten years.

365
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,867
After my dad's business failed,

366
00:20:34,126 --> 00:20:35,826
we lived in the annex
of the Chairman's house.

367
00:20:37,267 --> 00:20:40,873
I've had a crush on him for a long time.

368
00:20:43,267 --> 00:20:46,446
I think I was 21 when I confessed.

369
00:20:48,273 --> 00:20:49,415
But he rejected me.

370
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:53,118
He said he was someone...

371
00:20:53,118 --> 00:20:55,266
who could never love anyone.

372
00:20:57,267 --> 00:20:59,425
Not long after that, he went abroad,

373
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:02,428
and everything stopped.

374
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:04,630
Wait a minute, Manager Seo.

375
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:08,470
Why are you telling me all this?

376
00:21:09,167 --> 00:21:10,369
Will you just listen?

377
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:14,173
At the very least,
I think you should know.

378
00:21:16,967 --> 00:21:18,978
After he joined Kangsu Construction,

379
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:22,367
my feelings for him grew again,

380
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:27,576
much deeper and stronger
than ten years ago.

381
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:31,457
I'm sorry, Manager Seo,
but I won't listen anymore.

382
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,361
I'm not feeling well right now.

383
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:37,263
Then...

384
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,667
Please take good care of my Gyeol.

385
00:21:43,667 --> 00:21:46,967
As you know, once this competition ends,

386
00:21:46,967 --> 00:21:48,474
he'll go back to where he belongs.

387
00:21:49,467 --> 00:21:52,812
Until then, please be there for him...

388
00:21:53,173 --> 00:21:54,413
and keep him from being lonely.

389
00:21:55,713 --> 00:21:58,751
I don't think that's something...

390
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,153
you should be asking me to do.

391
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,467
What?

392
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:07,126
<i>Before this moment passes</i>

393
00:22:07,660 --> 00:22:10,600
<i>Enjoy it</i>

394
00:22:10,600 --> 00:22:13,499
<i>This world made just for me</i>

395
00:22:14,569 --> 00:22:17,169
Don't the lyrics of this song
really speak to you?

396
00:22:17,346 --> 00:22:18,346
Sure, I guess.

397
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:21,607
But why are you so full of energy today?

398
00:22:22,133 --> 00:22:24,933
I don't know.
It's like everything's on my side.

399
00:22:25,086 --> 00:22:28,680
You know what they say,
"You make your own luck."

400
00:22:28,839 --> 00:22:31,800
Lately, I feel like the whole universe...

401
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:33,853
revolves around me.

402
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:35,521
What do you mean?

403
00:22:35,779 --> 00:22:38,946
You know how Mother thought
she'd found her daughter?

404
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,460
That turned out to be a bust.

405
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:43,467
Really?

406
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:47,633
Poor Madam. She must've been so hopeful.

407
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:52,137
But is that really such good news for you?

408
00:22:52,137 --> 00:22:53,672
Of course it is.

409
00:22:53,780 --> 00:22:56,372
We almost had to split everything
into fractions of fractions...

410
00:22:56,372 --> 00:22:57,372
Sis, come in.

411
00:22:58,867 --> 00:23:00,312
Kang Yeon Ja, you're here.

412
00:23:00,312 --> 00:23:01,480
Welcome, ma'am.

413
00:23:02,406 --> 00:23:04,983
Welcome, Mrs. Cho.

414
00:23:06,567 --> 00:23:07,567
Excuse me?

415
00:23:08,667 --> 00:23:11,167
You got here early, Min Ho's mom.

416
00:23:11,167 --> 00:23:13,859
Yes,
I wanted to practice the new choreography.

417
00:23:14,167 --> 00:23:16,429
Did you get much practice in, madam?

418
00:23:17,167 --> 00:23:19,867
Why do you keep calling me madam?
Just call me by my name.

419
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:21,267
How could I do that?

420
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,870
Your husband
is my husband's executive assistant.

421
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:26,639
I should call you madam.

422
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:31,710
Just call her that.
Sounds like she likes hearing it.

423
00:23:32,467 --> 00:23:33,913
When did I say that?

424
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,983
Stand in the center.

425
00:23:37,267 --> 00:23:41,354
No, you take this spot.

426
00:23:41,599 --> 00:23:44,566
I'll graciously step aside
with my ocean-deep heart.

427
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:46,726
What's gotten into you?

428
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,329
By the way, Yeon Ja,
that tea you gave me yesterday...

429
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,667
smelled wonderful. What was it?

430
00:23:52,667 --> 00:23:55,468
Burdock tea. I roasted it myself.

431
00:23:55,772 --> 00:23:58,737
No wonder.
You'll have to teach me sometime.

432
00:24:00,067 --> 00:24:02,467
Seriously? You met her without me?

433
00:24:03,067 --> 00:24:04,310
What's your intention?

434
00:24:04,867 --> 00:24:06,067
What intention?

435
00:24:08,349 --> 00:24:09,867
- Hello.
- Hello.

436
00:24:09,867 --> 00:24:10,867
- Hello.
- Hello.

437
00:24:10,867 --> 00:24:12,218
- Hello.
- Hello.

438
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:17,700
- Ready?
- Yes.

439
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,886
Shall we enjoy ourselves again today?

440
00:24:19,886 --> 00:24:21,153
- Yes!
- Yes!

441
00:24:25,012 --> 00:24:27,399
Ready, five, six, start.

442
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:39,612
- The car is ready.
- Good.

443
00:24:40,867 --> 00:24:42,167
Hello, Chairman.

444
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:45,267
Good. Settling into work all right?

445
00:24:45,967 --> 00:24:47,420
I'm trying my best.

446
00:24:48,567 --> 00:24:50,723
Mother still can't get out of bed today?

447
00:24:51,126 --> 00:24:54,226
She's doing better than yesterday,
so don't worry too much.

448
00:24:54,767 --> 00:24:55,867
Goodness.

449
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:58,900
She must've been devastated.
It's already been four days.

450
00:24:59,719 --> 00:25:02,868
Don't go anywhere today.
Stay by Mother's side.

451
00:25:03,639 --> 00:25:06,106
Is Madam ill?

452
00:25:06,667 --> 00:25:07,973
I'll explain on the way.

453
00:25:12,467 --> 00:25:15,167
Mr. Cho, as you probably saw in my notes,

454
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:18,484
don't forget the heated seat for CEO Ko
on the way to work.

455
00:25:18,484 --> 00:25:20,719
Excuse me? The heated seat?

456
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:24,724
The seat warmer.

457
00:25:24,967 --> 00:25:28,027
CEO Ko has hemorrhoids.

458
00:25:28,827 --> 00:25:30,696
Seriously...

459
00:25:31,964 --> 00:25:32,964
I'll get going.

460
00:25:34,400 --> 00:25:35,400
I'll take my leave.

461
00:25:35,767 --> 00:25:37,600
Bonne journée. Have a nice day.

462
00:25:38,700 --> 00:25:39,905
Bonjour, my foot.

463
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:44,067
When did I say bonjour?

464
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:46,712
I said bonne journée. "Have a nice day."

465
00:25:47,839 --> 00:25:49,848
Chairman,

466
00:25:50,067 --> 00:25:52,700
would you like to take a walk
through the garden with me?

467
00:25:52,700 --> 00:25:54,853
The roses are in full bloom.

468
00:25:54,853 --> 00:25:56,420
Sure, why not?

469
00:25:58,167 --> 00:26:01,494
Please put these in Madam's room.

470
00:26:02,767 --> 00:26:03,767
Bonjour...

471
00:26:07,867 --> 00:26:10,467
She needs to get better and go out again,

472
00:26:10,467 --> 00:26:12,304
so I can open the safe.

473
00:26:13,660 --> 00:26:15,708
Maid, did you finish making porridge?

474
00:26:16,475 --> 00:26:18,977
(Kangsu Construction)

475
00:26:32,300 --> 00:26:33,967
I told you to get off
where you usually do.

476
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:35,394
What if someone sees us?

477
00:26:35,394 --> 00:26:38,230
We got here 30 minutes early.
Who's going to see us?

478
00:26:40,067 --> 00:26:41,967
And I'm a patient, remember?

479
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,671
You're not the only one with a cold.

480
00:26:46,267 --> 00:26:48,400
Can I ask you a favor? Today,

481
00:26:48,567 --> 00:26:51,176
could you please be careful
with the coughing?

482
00:26:51,176 --> 00:26:54,709
Like I can control when I cough.

483
00:26:54,867 --> 00:26:56,200
Go on before someone sees us.

484
00:27:31,283 --> 00:27:34,286
(Our Happy Days)

485
00:27:34,453 --> 00:27:37,800
Your daughter and Team Manager Ko
seem to be dating.

486
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,437
That can't be true.
I think you've misunderstood.

487
00:27:40,437 --> 00:27:42,094
He's leaving for the U.S. in a few months.

488
00:27:42,094 --> 00:27:44,200
I wonder what got into him.

489
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:46,067
I'm going upstairs to pack some things.

490
00:27:46,067 --> 00:27:48,100
I left a lot behind
when I moved out in a hurry.

491
00:27:50,202 --> 00:27:53,200
Honey, where have you been?
Do you know how worried I was?

492
00:27:53,200 --> 00:27:56,208
Eun Hyeong, let's get a divorce.

493
00:27:56,542 --> 00:27:58,210
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
